      },
      "lineNbr": 1070,
      "author": {
        "id": 1233742
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-10T00:50:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No dispatch required, since all of the Renderer APIs are expected to be called on a thread with the OpenGL context bound.  The only time it was required was to get back to the main thread after loading the texture data.\n\nI agree, having a shared context would be good in the future to simplify the loader thread.",
      "parentUuid": "762669af_8bee8338",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1070,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 1070,
        "endChar": 1
      },
